        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 8:59PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 859 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles southeast of Yuma to 12 miles southwest
of Eckley to 17 miles northeast of Cope. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

These storms will remain over mainly rural areas of central Yuma
County, including the following locations... Heartstrong.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
